  "An equation that contradicts another equation": "",
  "An equation that has a unique solution": "",
  "An equation with all coefficients equal to zero": "",
  "An equation that provides no new information because it is a linear combination of other equations": "",
  "A redundant equation is implied by the other equations in the system. Removing it does not change the solution set. In REF, it reduces to the zero row [0, ..., 0 | 0].": "",
  "What does the 'Rouche-Capelli theorem' state about consistency?": "",
  "A system is consistent if and only if the rank of the coefficient matrix equals the rank of the augmented matrix": "",
  "A system is consistent if and only if the determinant is nonzero": "",
  "A system is always consistent when it is homogeneous": "",
  "A system is consistent if the number of equations equals the number of unknowns": "",
  "The Rouche-Capelli theorem says Ax = b is consistent if and only if rank(A) = rank([A|b]). If the augmented matrix has a higher rank, a contradiction row exists and the system is inconsistent.": "",
